1 olive oil
1 tomato
1 cucumber
½ packet ciabatta
1 packet chicken breast
1 packet creamy pesto dressing
1 tsp water
1 bag Mixed Leaves
1 clove garlic
½ packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
½ sachet Italian Herbs

Finely chop garlic. Roughly chop tomato. Thinly
slice cucumber into half-moons. Tear ciabatta
(see ingredients) into small chunks. Cut chicken
breast into 2cm chunks. In a medium bowl,
combine garlic, Italian herbs (see ingredients) and
a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.
Add chicken and toss to coat.

Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat
with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook ciabatta, stirring
occasionally, until golden and crisp, 4-5 minutes.
Season to taste, then transfer to a large bowl.

In a small bowl, add creamy pesto dressing, the
water and a drizzle of olive oil. Season and stir to
combine. Set aside.

Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with
a drizzle of olive oil. Cook chicken, tossing, until
cooked through, 5-6 minutes. Remove from the
heat.

TIP: Cook the chicken in batches if your pan is
getting crowded!

To the croutons, add mixed leaves, tomato,
cucumber, grated Parmesan cheese (see
ingredients) and chicken. Toss to combine, then
drizzle with pesto dressing.

TIP: You can serve the chicken on the side if you
prefer!

To serve, divide Italian herbed chicken and crouton
salad with creamy pesto dressing between bowls.